    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-25T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="823"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d823">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/6–2554: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Eighteenth Restricted Session on Indochina, Geneva, June 25, 3
                        p.m.: The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-25T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 25, 1954—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 526. Repeated information Paris 503,
                    Saigon 214. At recess today’s restricted session, <persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                        >Chauvel</persName> expressed extreme disappointment over <persName
                        corresp="#p_KVV1">Kuznetsov</persName>‘s turn-down of <persName
                        corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName>‘s proposal for small meetings of experts
                    from certain delegations to study various proposals on armistice measures and
                    controls and <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName>‘s other suggestion
                    that <hi rend="italic">ad hoc</hi> committees be formed from time to time to
                    study specific armistice problems. <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName>
                    disagreed with <persName corresp="#p_KVV1">Kuznetsov</persName>‘s proposal that
                    the 9 delegation chiefs meet to discuss control measures with fewer experts
                    present than at recent sessions: A sort of a restricted session.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> thought at next session he would
                    present a detailed paper on functions and powers of the control measures in
                    answer to the Russian proposal of June 14 which is the only detailed paper on
                    the subject to date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
